    "Reason : 1 - In the absence of a Flood Risk Assessment and Sustainable Drainage Strategy, the proposals would result in increase in risk of flooding within the functional floodplain in the locality. It would be contrary to, in particular, Merton Sites and Policies Plan 2014 polices DM F1 and DM F2, Merton Core Strategy 2011 Policy CS16 and the Environmental Agency's Standing Advice.",
    "Reason : 2 - By reason of combined unsatisfactory siting, loss of front boundary treatment and layout, the proposed front garden parking increases visual permeability into a predominantly hard surfaced area and results in an unsafe form of vehicular access in close proximity to road junction to the detriment of the highway and pedestrian safety.  The scheme is contrary to, in particular, Merton Core Strategy 2011 Policy CS20 and CS14 and Policy DM T3, DM D2of Site and Policies Plan 2014.  "
